
                               XF86SETUP README
                               ----------------

   *WARNING!* This program will now modify your X configuration! Changing
   the mouse device will update the symlinks as soon as you press Apply.
   Also, if you run the program to completion, your old XF86Config file
   will be renamed to XF86Config.bak and a newly generated file will be put
   in its place. However, pressing the Abort button at any time will exit
   without changing your XF86Config file.

NOTES ON BUILDING

   The _xkbui_ library should be built first. To build it, copy or move the
   sources to the directory ".../xc/lib/xkbui". Then from that directory
   type:

	  make Makefile; make depend; make
  
   The rest of the package should be installed in a directory parallel to
   the "xf86config" sources, i.e. "XF86Setup" should be a subdirectory of
   ".../Xserver/hw/xfree86".

   You need to edit the "Imakefile" to make sure it contains the correct
   names for the tcl and tk library files and, if needed, the path to the
   tcl include files. Then type:

	  make Makefile; make includes; make depend; make
  
   If you wish to run it from the source directory without installing, you
   need to set the environment variable "XF86SETUPLIB" to point to the
   source directory.

